{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876578980,"sessionID":"ses_285821295ffeF8N6eB6GIv9su3","part":{"id":"prt_d7a7e0d02001wfIV4iAoZW77R5","messageID":"msg_d7a7dfd97001R0kc6RigjJspgc","sessionID":"ses_285821295ffeF8N6eB6GIv9su3","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_ba2c5f834a8c44ecb28e72db","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-029: SDK HTTP ň║Ľň▒éň«óŠłĚšź»\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Implement the HTTP client layer for the AgentCube Python SDK, providing low-level HTTP communication for Control Plane (Workload Manager) and Data Plane (Router) operations with connection pooling, timeout management, and session header handling.\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: ### Background\n10: \n11: The AgentCube Python SDK requires reliable HTTP communication with two backend services:\n12: \n13: - **Control Plane (Workload Manager)**: Session lifecycle (create/delete code interpreter sessions)\n14: - **Data Plane (Router)**: Code execution, file operations, and agent invocations\n15: \n16: The HTTP layer must handle:\n17: 1. Connection pooling for efficient resource usage\n18: 2. Configurable timeouts (connect + read)\n19: 3. Authentication token injection\n20: 4. Session header management (`x-agentcube-session-id`)\n21: 5. Error handling with appropriate exceptions\n22: \n23: ### Goal\n24: \n25: Implement a robust HTTP client layer that:\n26: - Provides `ControlPlaneClient` for Workload Manager communication\n27: - Provides `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` for Router communication\n28: - Handles connection pooling with `requests.Session` and `HTTPAdapter`\n29: - Manages timeouts consistently across all clients\n30: - Follows the SDK's HTTP contract specifications\n31: \n32: ### Value\n33: \n34: - **Reliability**: Consistent timeout and error handling\n35: - **Performance**: Connection pooling reduces latency\n36: - **Maintainability**: Centralized HTTP logic\n37: - **Developer Experience**: Clear API contracts\n38: \n39: ---\n40: \n41: ## Scope\n42: \n43: ### In-Scope\n44: \n45: | Component | Path | Description |\n46: |-----------|------|-------------|\n47: | ControlPlaneClient | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | Workload Manager HTTP client |\n48: | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | Router CI operations |\n49: | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | Router agent invocation |\n50: | create_session | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | Session with pooling |\n51: | read_token_from_file | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | Token file reading |\n52: | Exception classes | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Error types |\n53: \n54: ### Out-of-Scope\n55: \n56: - High-level client implementations (CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient)\n57: - Async HTTP support\n58: - Retry logic / circuit breaker\n59: - Authentication beyond token file\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ## Impact Analysis\n64: \n65: ### Dependencies\n66: \n67: | Dependency | Purpose | Status |\n68: |------------|---------|--------|\n69: | `requests` | HTTP client | Required |\n70: | `PyJWT>=2.0.0` | JWT handling | Required |\n71: | `cryptography` | Crypto operations | Required |\n72: \n73: ### Upstream\n74: \n75: - `python-sdk/design.md` ÔÇö HTTP client specifications\n76: - `python-sdk/spec.md` ÔÇö HTTP contract requirements\n77: \n78: ### Downstream Consumers\n79: \n80: 1. **CodeInterpreterClient** ÔÇö Uses ControlPlaneClient and CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n81: 2. **AgentRuntimeClient** ÔÇö Uses AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n82: 3. **SDK users** ÔÇö Indirect consumers through high-level clients\n83: \n84: ### Risks\n85: \n86: | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n87: |------|----------|------------|\n88: | Workload Manager unavailable | Medium | Timeout handling, clear error messages |\n89: | Token file missing | Low | Empty token (anonymous), warning log |\n90: | Connection pool exhaustion | Medium | Configurable pool size |\n91: \n92: ---\n93: \n94: ## Alternatives Considered\n95: \n96: ### Option 1: httpx for async support (Not Selected)\n97: \n98: **Pros**: Native async/await, sync/async unified API\n99: **Cons**: Adds new dependency; sync `requests` sufficient for current needs\n100: \n101: ### Option 2: urllib3 directly (Not Selected)\n102: \n103: **Pros**: Lower-level control\n104: **Cons**: More boilerplate; `requests` provides better abstraction\n105: \n106: ### Option 3: aiohttp (Not Selected)\n107: \n108: **Pros**: Async-first design\n109: **Cons**: Async not in scope; different API paradigm\n110: \n111: ### Option 4: requests with HTTPAdapter (Selected)\n112: \n113: **Pros**: Existing dependency, connection pooling, familiar API, timeout handling\n114: **Cons**: Sync-only\n115: \n116: ---\n117: \n118: ## Technical Design\n119: \n120: ### HTTP Session Creation\n121: \n122: ```python\n123: def create_session(\n124:     pool_connections: int = 10,\n125:     pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n126: ) -> requests.Session:\n127:     \"\"\"Create requests.Session with HTTPAdapter for connection pooling.\"\"\"\n128: ```\n129: \n130: Mounts `HTTPAdapter` for both `http://` and `https://` schemes.\n131: \n132: ### ControlPlaneClient\n133: \n134: ```python\n135: class ControlPlaneClient:\n136:     def __init__(\n137:         self,\n138:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n139:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n140:         timeout: int = 120,\n141:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n142:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n143:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n144:     ): ...\n145: \n146:     def create_session(\n147:         self,\n148:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n149:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n150:         metadata: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n151:         ttl: int = 3600,\n152:     ) -> str: ...\n153: \n154:     def delete_session(self, session_id: str) -> bool: ...\n155: \n156:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n157: ```\n158: \n159: #### Control Plane HTTP Contract\n160: \n161: | Method | Path | Notes |\n162: |--------|------|-------|\n163: | POST | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | JSON body: `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `metadata` |\n164: | DELETE | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | 404 treated as success |\n165: \n166: **Headers:**\n167: - `Content-Type`: `application/json`\n168: - `Authorization`: `Bearer {token}` if token non-empty\n169: \n170: **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` on each request.\n171: \n172: **URL Resolution:**\n173: - `base_url` ÔćÉ `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env var\n174: \n175: **Token Resolution:**\n176: - `auth_token` or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n177: \n178: ### CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n179: \n180: ```python\n181: class CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n182:     def __init__(\n183:         self,\n184:         session_id: str,\n185:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n186:         namespace: Optional[str] = None,\n187:         cr_name: Optional[str] = None,\n188:         base_url: Optional[str] = None,\n189:         timeout: int = 120,\n190:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n191:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n192:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n193:     ): ...\n194: \n195:     def _request(self, method: str, endpoint: str, body: Optional[bytes] = None, **kwargs) -> requests.Response: ...\n196: \n197:     def execute_command(self, command: Union[str, List[str]], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n198:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n199:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n200:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n201:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None: ...\n202:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any: ...\n203:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n204: ```\n205: \n206: #### Data Plane (Code Interpreter) HTTP Contract\n207: \n208: **Base URL:**\n209: - If `base_url` provided: use directly\n210: - Otherwise: `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/`\n211: \n212: | Method | Relative path | Body / params |\n213: |--------|---------------|---------------|\n214: | POST | `api/execute` | JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` |\n215: | POST | `api/files` | JSON `{\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` |\n216: | POST | `api/files` (multipart) | `files={'file': ...}`, `data={'path', 'mode'}` |\n217: | GET | `api/files/{clean_path}` | `stream=True` for download |\n218: | GET | `api/files` | query `path` |\n219: \n220: **Headers:**\n221: - Default session header: `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n222: - JSON requests: `Content-Type: application/json`\n223: - Multipart upload: `x-agentcube-session-id` only\n224: \n225: **Note:** Router handles JWT; SDK does not set `Authorization` on data plane.\n226: \n227: ### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n228: \n229: ```python\n230: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n231:     SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n232: \n233:     def __init__(\n234:         self,\n235:         router_url: str,\n236:         namespace: str,\n237:         agent_name: str,\n238:         timeout: int = 120,\n239:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n240:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n241:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n242:     ): ...\n243: \n244:     def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str: ...\n245: \n246:     def invoke(\n247:         self,\n248:         session_id: str,\n249:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n250:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n251:     ) -> requests.Response: ...\n252: \n253:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n254: ```\n255: \n256: #### Data Plane (Agent Runtime) HTTP Contract\n257: \n258: **Base URL:**\n259: `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n260: \n261: | Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n262: |--------|-----|---------|------|\n263: | GET | `self.base_url` | (session default headers only) | ÔÇö |\n264: | POST | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n265: \n266: **Timeouts:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` where `timeout` for `invoke` read side is method argument or `self.timeout`.\n267: \n268: ### Token File Reading\n269: \n270: ```python\n271: def read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str:\n272:     \"\"\"Read token from file, return stripped contents or empty string on error.\"\"\"\n273: ```\n274: \n275: Returns file contents stripped, or `\"\"` on `FileNotFoundError`.\n276: \n277: ### Exception Hierarchy\n278: \n279: ```python\n280: class AgentCubeError(Exception):\n281:     \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n282:     pass\n283: \n284: class CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n285:     def __init__(self, exit_code, stderr, command=None):\n286:         self.exit_code = exit_code\n287:         self.stderr = stderr\n288:         self.command = command\n289:         super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n290: \n291: class SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n292:     \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"\"\"\n293:     pass\n294: \n295: class DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n296:     \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n297:     pass\n298: ```\n299: \n300: ---\n301: \n302: ## Implementation Plan\n303: \n304: ### Phase 1: Core HTTP Utilities\n305: \n306: - [ ] Create `agentcube/utils/http.py` ÔÇö `create_session()` with HTTPAdapter\n307: - [ ] Create `agentcube/utils/utils.py` ÔÇö `read_token_from_file()`\n308: - [ ] Create `agentcube/utils/log.py` ÔÇö `get_logger()`\n309: - [ ] Create `agentcube/utils/__init__.py` ÔÇö empty module marker\n310: \n311: ### Phase 2: Exception Classes\n312: \n313: - [ ] Create `agentcube/exceptions.py` ÔÇö exception hierarchy\n314: - [ ] Define `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, `DataPlaneError`\n315: \n316: ### Phase 3: ControlPlaneClient\n317: \n318: - [ ] Create `agentcube/clients/__init__.py`\n319: - [ ] Create `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n320: - [ ] Implement `create_session()` ÔÇö POST to Workload Manager\n321: - [ ] Implement `delete_session()` ÔÇö DELETE with 404-as-success handling\n322: - [ ] Implement token resolution (arg/env/file)\n323: - [ ] Add timeout handling\n324: \n325: ### Phase 4: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n326: \n327: - [ ] Create `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n328: - [ ] Implement base URL construction\n329: - [ ] Implement `_request()` ÔÇö low-level HTTP\n330: - [ ] Implement `execute_command()` ÔÇö POST to api/execute\n331: - [ ] Implement `write_file()` ÔÇö base64 upload\n332: - [ ] Implement `upload_file()` ÔÇö multipart upload\n333: - [ ] Implement `download_file()` ÔÇö streaming download\n334: - [ ] Implement `list_files()` ÔÇö GET with query\n335: - [ ] Add session header management\n336: \n337: ### Phase 5: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n338: \n339: - [ ] Create `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n340: - [ ] Implement base URL construction\n341: - [ ] Implement `bootstrap_session_id()` ÔÇö GET + header extraction\n342: - [ ] Implement `invoke()` ÔÇö POST JSON with session header\n343: - [ ] Add timeout handling\n344: \n345: ### Phase 6: Integration & Exports\n346: \n347: - [ ] Update `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` exports\n348: - [ ] Verify all clients work together\n349: \n350: ---\n351: \n352: ## Acceptance Criteria\n353: \n354: | ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n355: |----|----------|-----------------|\n356: | HTTP-001 | create_session with pooling | Session has HTTPAdapter mounted |\n357: | HTTP-002 | ControlPlaneClient create_session | POST with correct JSON body, returns sessionId |\n358: | HTTP-003 | ControlPlaneClient delete_session (404) | Returns True |\n359: | HTTP-004 | ControlPlaneClient token from file | Reads from default Kubernetes path |\n360: | HTTP-005 | DataPlaneClient execute_command | POST with correct JSON, timeout handling |\n361: | HTTP-006 | DataPlaneClient write_file | POST with base64 content |\n362: | HTTP-007 | DataPlaneClient upload_file | Multipart POST with session header |\n363: | HTTP-008 | DataPlaneClient download_file | Streaming GET |\n364: | HTTP-009 | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient bootstrap | GET extracts x-agentcube-session-id |\n365: | HTTP-010 | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient invoke | POST with correct headers |\n366: | HTTP-011 | Timeout tuple format | (connect_timeout, read_timeout) |\n367: | HTTP-012 | Session header case | Lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id` |\n368: \n369: ---\n370: \n371: ## Timeline Estimate\n372: \n373: | Phase | Effort |\n374: |-------|--------|\n375: | Core HTTP Utilities | 1 hour |\n376: | Exception Classes | 0.5 hours |\n377: | ControlPlaneClient | 1.5 hours |\n378: | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient | 2.5 hours |\n379: | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient | 1.5 hours |\n380: | Integration & Tests | 2 hours |\n381: | **Total** | **9 hours** |\n382: \n383: ---\n384: \n385: ## Relationship to AR-027 / AR-028\n386: \n387: AR-027 (SDK CodeInterpreterClient) and AR-028 (SDK AgentRuntimeClient) are high-level clients that consume this HTTP layer.\n388: \n389: AR-029 provides the foundation:\n390: - Connection pooling\n391: - Timeout management\n392: - HTTP contracts\n393: - Session header handling\n394: - Error types\n395: \n396: The high-level clients delegate HTTP operations to these low-level clients, providing developer-friendly APIs on top.\n\n(End of file - total 396 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-029: SDK HTTP ň║Ľň▒éň«óŠłĚšź»\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement the HTTP client layer for the AgentCube Python SDK, providing low-level HTTP communication for Control Plane (Workload Manager) and Data Plane (Router) operations with connection pooling, timeout management, and session header handling.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nThe AgentCube Python SDK requires reliable HTTP communication with two backend services:\n\n- **Control Plane (Workload Manager)**: Session lifecycle (create/delete code interpreter sessions)\n- **Data Plane (Router)**: Code execution, file operations, and agent invocations\n\nThe HTTP layer must handle:\n1. Connection pooling for efficient resource usage\n2. Configurable timeouts (connect + read)\n3. Authentication token injection\n4. Session header management (`x-agentcube-session-id`)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775876578951,"end":1775876578978}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876578984,"sessionID":"ses_285821295ffeF8N6eB6GIv9su3","part":{"id":"prt_d7a7e12c9001v0NWeIJhzLpmic","messageID":"msg_d7a7dfd97001R0kc6RigjJspgc","sessionID":"ses_285821295ffeF8N6eB6GIv9su3","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_411b0febd04e4e38a1ea3acc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/ci-cd/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/ci-cd/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # CI/CD Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Automate validation on pull requests (build, lint, tests, codegen drift checks), publish container images on pushes to `main` and version tags, run end-to-end tests on Kind, exercise the Python SDK, and enforce spelling and copyright consistency.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Pull request build verification\n9: The system SHALL build the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Docker build in CI\n12: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n13: - **WHEN** the ÔÇťAgentcube CI WorkflowÔÇŁ job runs\n14: - **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository, set up Docker Buildx, verify `docker`/`buildx` versions, and run `make docker-build`\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Go lint on changed Go code\n17: The system SHALL run `make lint` (golangci-lint) when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*`.\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Path-filtered lint\n20: - **GIVEN** a pull request and path filter matches `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, or `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n21: - **WHEN** the Lint workflow runs\n22: - **THEN** it SHALL use Go `1.24` and execute `make lint`\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Code generation check\n25: The system SHALL verify generated artifacts match `make gen-all` when API, hack, workflow, or Makefile inputs change.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Regenerate and diff\n28: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, or `Makefile`\n29: - **WHEN** the Codegen Check workflow runs with Go `1.24.4`\n30: - **THEN** it SHALL run `make gen-check` (which runs `gen-all` and `git diff --exit-code`)\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Go test coverage reporting\n33: The system SHALL run race-enabled coverage tests on `pkg/...` for qualifying pull requests and merge groups, optionally uploading to Codecov.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Coverage command\n36: - **GIVEN** path filter `coverage` matches (broad glob excluding some media/docs per workflow)\n37: - **WHEN** the Test Coverage job runs with Go `1.24`\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...` and upload `coverage.out` as an artifact\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: E2E testing on Kind\n41: The system SHALL run `make e2e` in CI using a Kind-capable Ubuntu runner, capturing logs on failure.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: E2E job lifecycle\n44: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n45: - **WHEN** the E2E workflow runs\n46: - **THEN** it SHALL set `ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`, install Kind tool `v0.30.0` (`install_only: true`), run `make e2e` with Go `1.23`, upload `e2e-logs` on failure, and always run `make e2e-clean`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: Python SDK unit tests\n49: The system SHALL run pytest for the SDK when `sdk-python/**` changes.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Editable install and pytest\n52: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `sdk-python/**`\n53: - **WHEN** the Python SDK Tests job runs with Python `3.12` in `sdk-python/`\n54: - **THEN** it SHALL `pip install pytest`, `pip install -e .`, and run `python -m pytest tests/ -v`\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: Python lint\n57: The system SHALL run Ruff from repository root using `pyproject.toml` when Python-touching paths change.\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Ruff check\n60: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, or the workflow file\n61: - **WHEN** the Python Lint job runs with Python `3.10`\n62: - **THEN** it SHALL `pip install ruff` and run `python3 -m ruff check . --config pyproject.toml`\n63: \n64: ### Requirement: Spelling check (codespell)\n65: The system SHALL run codespell on the repository for pull requests to `main` or `release-*`, temporarily moving files that cause false positives.\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Codespell invocation\n68: - **GIVEN** checkout complete\n69: - **WHEN** codespell runs after backup/remove of `pyproject.toml`, `package-lock.json`, `package.json` at repo root (and nested copies per `find`)\n70: - **THEN** it SHALL use `pip install codespell` and run codespell with `--check-filenames`, specified `--skip` globs, and `--ignore-words-list fo,nam,te,notin,NotIn` on `.`, then restore backed-up files\n71: \n72: ### Requirement: Copyright header check\n73: The system SHALL ensure `make gen-copyright` produces no git diff when applicable files change.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Copyright workflow\n76: - **GIVEN** path filter marks `copyright` (all paths minus exclusions for md/svg/png/docs/.github per workflow)\n77: - **WHEN** the job runs\n78: - **THEN** it SHALL install `moreutils` (`sponge`), run `make gen-copyright`, and `git diff --exit-code`\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: Release image publication\n81: The system SHALL build and push multi-architecture images for workloadmanager, router, and picod to GitHub Container Registry on pushes to `main` and on semantic version tags.\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Tag selects image tag\n84: - **GIVEN** a `push` event\n85: - **WHEN** `github.ref_type` is `tag`, environment `TAG` SHALL be `github.ref_name`; otherwise `TAG` SHALL be `latest`\n86: - **THEN** the job SHALL log in to `ghcr.io` with `GITHUB_TOKEN` and run `make docker-buildx-push*`, setting `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` and per-image `*_IMAGE=<name>:${TAG}`\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Workflow approval for first-time contributors\n89: The system SHALL optionally approve pending workflow runs for pull requests from repeat contributors or those labeled `ok-to-test`.\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Approve action_required runs\n92: - **GIVEN** `pull_request_target` on `main` or `release-**` with label/sync events\n93: - **WHEN** the contributor is not first-time (more than one PR) or PR has `ok-to-test`\n94: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL list workflow runs for the head SHA with `status: action_required` and call `approveWorkflowRun` for each\n\n(End of file - total 94 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# CI/CD Specification\n\n## Purpose\nAutomate validation on pull requests (build, lint, tests, codegen drift checks), publish container images on pushes to `main` and version tags, run end-to-end tests on Kind, exercise the Python SDK, and enforce spelling and copyright consistency.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Pull request build verification\nThe system SHALL build the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n\n#### Scenario: Docker build in CI\n- **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n- **WHEN** the ÔÇťAgentcube CI WorkflowÔÇŁ job runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository, set up Docker Buildx, verify `docker`/`buildx` versions, and run `make docker-build`\n\n### Requirement: Go lint on changed Go code\nThe system SHALL run `make lint` (golangci-lint) when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*`.\n\n#### Scenario: Path-filtered lint\n- **GIVEN** a pull request and path filter matches `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, or `.github/workflows/lint.yml`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/ci-cd/spec.md","time":{"start":1775876578956,"end":1775876578983}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876578988,"sessionID":"ses_285821295ffeF8N6eB6GIv9su3","part":{"id":"prt_d7a7e18d2001z4YNl12uyZzfFp","messageID":"msg_d7a7dfd97001R0kc6RigjJspgc","sessionID":"ses_285821295ffeF8N6eB6GIv9su3","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_319ace917dba462e8cd64681","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/ci-cd/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/ci-cd/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube CI/CD ÔÇö Design\n2: \n3: Sources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/.github/workflows/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/test/`, and (for Make targets) `/tmp/agentcube-ref/Makefile`.\n4: \n5: ## GitHub Actions workflows (summary table)\n6: \n7: | Filename | Workflow `name` | Trigger events | Path filters (dorny/paths-filter or notes) | Jobs | Key steps | Env vars (job/step) | Secrets |\n8: |----------|-----------------|----------------|---------------------------------------------|------|-----------|---------------------|---------|\n9: | `main.yml` | Agentcube CI Workflow | `pull_request` Ôćĺ `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `build` | Checkout; Docker Buildx setup; verify Docker; `make docker-build` | ÔÇö | ÔÇö |\n10: | `e2e.yml` | Agentcube E2E Tests | `pull_request` Ôćĺ `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `e2e-test` | Checkout; Go 1.23; `helm/kind-action@v1` **install_only** Kind v0.30.0, `cluster_name: agentcube-e2e`; `export ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`; `make e2e`; on failure upload `e2e-logs/`; `always` Ôćĺ `make e2e-clean` | `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (shell) | ÔÇö |\n11: | `lint.yml` | Lint | `pull_request` Ôćĺ `main`, `release-*` | `lint`: `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | `golangci` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24; `make lint` | ÔÇö | ÔÇö |\n12: | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK Tests | `pull_request`, `merge_group` | `sdk`: `sdk-python/**` | `python-sdk-tests` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.12 in `sdk-python/`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` | Default `working-directory: sdk-python` | ÔÇö |\n13: | `python-lint.yml` | Python Lint | `pull_request` Ôćĺ `main`, `release-*` | `python`: `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, workflow self | `python_lint` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.10; `pip install ruff`; `ruff check . --config pyproject.toml` | ÔÇö | ÔÇö |\n14: | `test-coverage.yml` | Test Coverage | `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call` | `coverage`: `**` minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png` | `coverage` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: free disk space; Go 1.24; `go test` with coverage; step summary; Codecov upload; artifact `go-coverage` | `CODECOV_TOKEN` passed to Codecov action when present | `secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN` (optional; declared for `workflow_call`) |\n15: | `codegen-check.yml` | Codegen Check | `pull_request` Ôćĺ `main`, `release-*` | `codegen`: `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` | `codegen-check` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24.4; `make gen-check` | ÔÇö | ÔÇö |\n16: | `copyright-check.yml` | Copyright Check | `pull_request` Ôćĺ `main`, `release-*` | `copyright`: all files except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**` | `build` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: `apt install moreutils`; `make gen-copyright`; `git diff --exit-code` | ÔÇö | ÔÇö |\n17: | `codespell.yml` | Codespell | `pull_request` Ôćĺ `main`, `release-*` | *(none ÔÇö scans tree after temporarily removing some manifests)* | `codespell` | Backup/remove `pyproject.toml`, `package.json`, `package-lock.json`; `pip install codespell`; `codespell` with `--check-filenames`, `--skip`, `--ignore-words-list`; restore files | ÔÇö | ÔÇö |\n18: | `build-push-release.yml` | Build and Push Release Images | `push` Ôćĺ `main`; `push` tags `v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*` | *(none)* | `build-and-push` | Checkout; Go 1.24.4; Buildx; `docker/login-action` to `ghcr.io`; set `TAG` from ref; `make docker-buildx-push` (workload manager), `docker-buildx-push-router`, `docker-buildx-push-picod` with `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `TAG`, `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` | `GITHUB_TOKEN` (registry login) |\n19: | `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify Plugin Publish | `push` tags `dify-plugin/v*` | *(none)* | `publish` | Download `dify-plugin` CLI 0.0.6; install `yq`; read `manifest.yaml`; package plugin; checkout `author/dify-plugins` with token; move `.difypkg`; branch, commit, push; `gh pr create` to `langgenius/dify-plugins` | `GH_TOKEN` on PR step | `PLUGIN_ACTION` (repo checkout + `gh`; cross-repo PR) |\n20: | `workflows-approve.yml` | Approve Workflows | `pull_request_target` types `labeled`, `synchronize` Ôćĺ `main`, `release-**` | *(logic: first-time contributor vs `ok-to-test` label)* | `approve` | `github-script`: list contributor PRs; if not first-time or has `ok-to-test`, list `action_required` workflow runs for SHA and approve | ÔÇö | `GITHUB_TOKEN` |\n21: \n22: ### Workflow notes\n23: \n24: - **`e2e.yml`**: Uses Kind action with `install_only: true` so the cluster is created by `run_e2e.sh` (`kind create cluster`), avoiding double-creation.\n25: - **`test-coverage.yml`**: `workflow_call` declares `CODECOV_TOKEN` optional for reusable invocation; PR runs use the repo secret when configured.\n26: - **`build-push-release.yml`**: Uses older action major versions (`checkout@v3`, `setup-go@v4`, `buildx@v2`) than most other workflows.\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ## E2E test setup (`test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`)\n31: \n32: ### Kind cluster\n33: \n34: | Item | Value / behavior |\n35: |------|------------------|\n36: | Default cluster name | `E2E_CLUSTER_NAME` Ôćĺ `agentcube-e2e` |\n37: | Creation | `kind create cluster --name \"${E2E_CLUSTER_NAME}\"` if missing; if exists and `E2E_CLEAN_CLUSTER=true` (default), delete then recreate |\n38: | CI alignment | `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` installs Kind **v0.30.0** via `helm/kind-action@v1` (`install_only: true`) |\n39: | Skip setup | `E2E_SKIP_SETUP=true` skips `run_setup` and assumes an existing cluster |\n40: \n41: ### CRD / agent-sandbox installation\n42: \n43: Applied via `kubectl apply --validate=false` after downloading release assets (URLs built from `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION`, default **`v0.1.1`**):\n44: \n45: 1. `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox/releases/download/${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}/manifest.yaml`\n46: 2. `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox/releases/download/${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}/extensions.yaml`\n47: \n48: ### Images pre-pulled and loaded into Kind\n49: \n50: - `registry.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/agent-sandbox-controller:${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}`\n51: - `python:3.9-slim` (echo agent workload)\n52: \n53: Local images built and loaded:\n54: \n55: - `make docker-build` Ôćĺ default `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE` **`workloadmanager:latest`**\n56: - `make docker-build-router` Ôćĺ **`agentcube-router:latest`**\n57: - `make docker-build-picod` Ôćĺ **`picod:latest`**\n58: - `REDIS_IMAGE` default **`redis:7-alpine`** (Deployment + Service in namespace)\n59: \n60: ### Helm (AgentCube chart)\n61: \n62: | Item | Value |\n63: |------|--------|\n64: | Chart path | `manifests/charts/base` |\n65: | Release / namespace | `agentcube` in `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (default `agentcube`), `--create-namespace` |\n66: | Redis addr | `redis.${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}.svc.cluster.local:6379`, password empty |\n67: | Workload manager image | `repository=workloadmanager`, `tag=latest` |\n68: | Router image | `repository=agentcube-router`, `tag=latest` |\n69: | Router RBAC | `router.rbac.create=true`, `router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router` |\n70: | Extra env (JSON via `--set-json`) | Workload manager: `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`, `JWT_KEY_SECRET_NAMESPACE=agentcube`; Router: `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n71: | Wait | `helm upgrade --install ... --wait` |\n72: \n73: ### Kubernetes fixtures applied during setup\n74: \n75: | Path | Purpose |\n76: |------|---------|\n77: | `test/e2e/echo_agent.yaml` | `AgentRuntime` `echo-agent` in `agentcube` |\n78: | Generated from `echo_agent.yaml` (sed) | `echo-agent-short-ttl` with `sessionTimeout: \"30s\"` for TTL tests |\n79: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter.yaml` | `CodeInterpreter` `e2e-code-interpreter` in `agentcube` |\n80: \n81: Warm-pool Go tests apply `e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml` at runtime (not in initial `kubectl apply` list in the shell script).\n82: \n83: ### Port forwards and health checks\n84: \n85: - Workload manager: `kubectl port-forward svc/workloadmanager` Ôćĺ `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT` (default **8080**) Ôćĺ pod 8080\n86: - Router: `kubectl port-forward svc/agentcube-router` Ôćĺ `ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT` (default **8081**) Ôćĺ pod 8080\n87: - Readiness: `curl` to `http://localhost:${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT}/health` and `http://localhost:${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT}/health/live`\n88: \n89: ### Auth for tests\n90: \n91: - ServiceAccount `e2e-test` in `agentcube` + `ClusterRoleBinding` to `workloadmanager` clusterrole\n92: - API token: `kubectl create token e2e-test -n agentcube --duration=24h` Ôćĺ `API_TOKEN`\n93: \n94: ### Python venv for E2E\n95: \n96: - Directory: `E2E_VENV_DIR` (default `/tmp/agentcube-e2e-venv`)\n97: - `python3 -m venv`, `pip install -e ./sdk-python`, verify `import agentcube`\n98: \n99: ### Test commands invoked by `run_e2e.sh`\n100: \n101: **Go** (from repository root):\n102: \n103: ```bash\n104: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=\"http://localhost:${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT}\" \\\n105: ROUTER_URL=\"http://localhost:${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT}\" \\\n106: API_TOKEN=$API_TOKEN \\\n107: go test -v ./test/e2e/...\n108: ```\n109: \n110: **Python** (after `cd` to `test/e2e`):\n111: \n112: ```bash\n113: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=\"...\" ROUTER_URL=\"...\" API_TOKEN=$API_TOKEN \\\n114: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE=\"${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}\" \\\n115: \"$E2E_VENV_DIR/bin/python\" test_codeinterpreter.py\n116: ```\n117: \n118: (`test_codeinterpreter.py` uses `unittest.main()` and appends `--verbose` if missing.)\n119: \n120: ### Failure artifacts\n121: \n122: On test failure, `collect_component_logs` writes under `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (CI: `${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`): workload manager, router, and sandbox pod logs/describes.\n123: \n124: ---\n125: \n126: ## Test directory structure\n127: \n128: ```\n129: test/\n130: ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ OWNERS\n131: ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ e2e/\n132:     ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ README.md\n133:     ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ __init__.py\n134:     ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ run_e2e.sh\n135:     ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ e2e_test.go\n136:     ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ test_codeinterpreter.py\n137:     ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ echo_agent.yaml\n138:     ÔöťÔöÇÔöÇ e2e_code_interpreter.yaml\n139:     ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml\n140: ```\n141: \n142: ### Fixture paths (relative to repo root unless noted)\n143: \n144: | Fixture | Description |\n145: |---------|-------------|\n146: | `test/e2e/echo_agent.yaml` | Echo `AgentRuntime` for router invocation tests |\n147: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter.yaml` | Standard `CodeInterpreter` (`e2e-code-interpreter`, namespace `agentcube`) |\n148: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml` | `CodeInterpreter` with `warmPoolSize: 2` in `default` (loaded by Go tests from **package cwd** as `e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml`) |\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## Go test commands and flags in CI\n153: \n154: | Workflow / entrypoint | Command | Flags / notes |\n155: |------------------------|---------|----------------|\n156: | `test-coverage.yml` | `go test` | `-race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...` |\n157: | `e2e.yml` via `make e2e` Ôćĺ `run_e2e.sh` | `go test` | `-v ./test/e2e/...` with env `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `API_TOKEN` |\n158: \n159: ---\n160: \n161: ## Python test commands in CI\n162: \n163: | Workflow | Working dir | Command |\n164: |----------|-------------|---------|\n165: | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | `sdk-python` | `python -m pip install --upgrade pip`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` |\n166: | `e2e.yml` (via `run_e2e.sh`) | Invoked from `test/e2e/` | `\"$E2E_VENV_DIR/bin/python\" test_codeinterpreter.py` (unittest, verbosity 2) |\n167: \n168: ---\n169: \n170: ## Key Make targets referenced by CI\n171: \n172: | Target | Referenced in | Role |\n173: |--------|----------------|------|\n174: | `docker-build` | `main.yml`, `run_e2e.sh` | Build workload manager image |\n175: | `docker-build-router` | `run_e2e.sh` | Build router image |\n176: | `docker-build-picod` | `run_e2e.sh` | Build picod image |\n177: | `docker-buildx-push` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push workload manager image (`IMAGE_REGISTRY`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE=workloadmanager:${TAG}`) |\n178: | `docker-buildx-push-router` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push router image |\n179: | `docker-buildx-push-picod` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push picod image |\n180: | `e2e` | `e2e.yml` | Run `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` |\n181: | `e2e-clean` | `e2e.yml` | `kind delete cluster --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME)`; `rm -rf /tmp/agent-sandbox` |\n182: | `lint` | `lint.yml` | `golangci-lint` (project default) |\n183: | `gen-check` | `codegen-check.yml` | Verify generated code up to date |\n184: | `gen-copyright` | `copyright-check.yml` | Generate copyright headers for check |\n185: \n186: ---\n187: \n188: ## Additional reference: E2E README vs script\n189: \n190: `test/e2e/README.md` states Go **1.24+** and generic ÔÇťinstall CRDs and agent-sandboxÔÇŁ; the **CI workflow** pins Go **1.23** for E2E, and **run_e2e.sh** pins **agent-sandbox `v0.1.1`** by default (overridable via `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION`).\n\n(End of file - total 190 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube CI/CD ÔÇö Design\n\nSources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/.github/workflows/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/test/`, and (for Make targets) `/tmp/agentcube-ref/Makefile`.\n\n## GitHub Actions workflows (summary table)\n\n| Filename | Workflow `name` | Trigger events | Path filters (dorny/paths-filter or notes) | Jobs | Key steps | Env vars (job/step) | Secrets |\n|----------|-----------------|----------------|---------------------------------------------|------|-----------|---------------------|---------|\n| `main.yml` | Agentcube CI Workflow | `pull_request` Ôćĺ `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `build` | Checkout; Docker Buildx setup; verify Docker; `make docker-build` | ÔÇö | ÔÇö |\n| `e2e.yml` | Agentcube E2E Tests | `pull_request` Ôćĺ `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `e2e-test` | Checkout; Go 1.23; `helm/kind-action@v1` **install_only** Kind v0.30.0, `cluster_name: agentcube-e2e`; `export ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`; `make e2e`; on failure upload `e2e-logs/`; `always` Ôćĺ `make e2e-clean` | `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (shell) | ÔÇö |\n| `lint.yml` | Lint | `pull_request` Ôćĺ `main`, `release-*` | `lint`: `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | `golangci` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24; `make lint` | ÔÇö | ÔÇö |\n| `python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK Tests | `pull_request`, `merge_group` | `sdk`: `sdk-python/**` | `python-sdk-tests` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.12 in `sdk-python/`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` | Default `working-directory: sdk-python` | ÔÇö |\n| `python-lint.yml` | Python Lint | `pull_request` Ôćĺ `main`, `release-*` | `python`: `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, workflow self | `python_lint` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.10; `pip install ruff`; `ruff check . --config pyproject.toml` | ÔÇö | ÔÇö |\n| `test-coverage.yml` | Test Coverage | `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call` | `coverage`: `**` minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png` | `coverage` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: free disk space; Go 1.24; `go test` with coverage; step summary; Codecov upload; artifact `go-coverage` | `CODECOV_TOKEN` passed to Codecov action when present | `secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN` (optional; declared for `workflow_call`) |\n| `codegen-check.yml` | Codegen Check | `pull_request` Ôćĺ `main`, `release-*` | `codegen`: `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` | `codegen-check` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24.4; `make gen-check` | ÔÇö | ÔÇö |\n| `copyright-check.yml` | Copyright Check | `pull_request` Ôćĺ `main`, `release-*` | `copyright`: all files except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**` | `build` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: `apt install moreutils`; `make gen-copyright`; `git diff --exit-code` | ÔÇö | ÔÇö |\n| `codespell.yml` | Codespell | `pull_request` Ôćĺ `main`, `release-*` | *(none ÔÇö scans tree after temporarily removing some manifests)* | `codespell` | Backup/remove `pyproject.toml`, `package.json`, `package-lock.json`; `pip install codespell`; `codespell` with `--check-filenames`, `--skip`, `--ignore-words-list`; restore files | ÔÇö | ÔÇö |\n| `build-push-release.yml` | Build and Push Release Images | `push` Ôćĺ `main`; `push` tags `v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*` | *(none)* | `build-and-push` | Checkout; Go 1.24.4; Buildx; `docker/login-action` to `ghcr.io`; set `TAG` from ref; `make docker-buildx-push` (workload manager), `docker-buildx-push-router`, `docker-buildx-push-picod` with `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `TAG`, `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` | `GITHUB_TOKEN` (registry login) |\n| `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify Plugin Publish | `push` tags `dify-plugin/v*` | *(none)* | `publish` | Download `dify-plugin` CLI 0.0.6; install `yq`; read `manifest.yaml`; package plugin; checkout `author/dify-plugins` with token; move `.difypkg`; branch, commit, push; `gh pr create` to `langgenius/dify-plugins` | `GH_TOKEN` on PR step | `PLUGIN_ACTION` (repo checkout + `gh`; cross-repo PR) |\n| `workflows-approve.yml` | Approve Workflows | `pull_request_target` types `labeled`, `synchronize` Ôćĺ `main`, `release-**` | *(logic: first-time contributor vs `ok-to-test` label)* | `approve` | `github-script`: list contributor PRs; if not first-time or has `ok-to-test`, list `action_required` workflow runs for SHA and approve | ÔÇö | `GITHUB_TOKEN` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/ci-cd/design.md","time":{"start":1775876578958,"end":1775876578985}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775876579021,"sessionID":"ses_285821295ffeF8N6eB6GIv9su3","part":{"id":"prt_d7a7e1eab001EO3VK1UoXyPtrl","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7a7dfd97001R0kc6RigjJspgc","sessionID":"ses_285821295ffeF8N6eB6GIv9su3","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":20073,"input":5019,"output":213,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":14841}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775876584625,"sessionID":"ses_285821295ffeF8N6eB6GIv9su3","part":{"id":"prt_d7a7e34ae001bh2Warv5nxQsKY","messageID":"msg_d7a7e1eed0013D3kHezV4TZveL","sessionID":"ses_285821295ffeF8N6eB6GIv9su3","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876586463,"sessionID":"ses_285821295ffeF8N6eB6GIv9su3","part":{"id":"prt_d7a7e37db001j608o35CXmArT1","messageID":"msg_d7a7e1eed0013D3kHezV4TZveL","sessionID":"ses_285821295ffeF8N6eB6GIv9su3","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_e0e0b7cf2c624fbfab2905f5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/.sdd_prompt.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/.sdd_prompt.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: Write design.md with technical implementation details for the agentcube project:\n2: \n3: AR: AR-029 ÔÇö SDK HTTP ň║Ľň▒éň«óŠłĚšź»\n4: Module: sdk-python\n5: Language: Python\n6: Size: M\n7: \n8: Specs:\n9: --- python-sdk/design.md ---\n10: # AgentCube Python SDK ÔÇö Design\n11: \n12: Source root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/`.\n13: \n14: ## Package layout\n15: \n16: | Path | Role |\n17: |------|------|\n18: | `pyproject.toml` | Package `agentcube-sdk`, dependencies |\n19: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports |\n20: | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` |\n21: | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` |\n22: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception classes |\n23: | `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Re-exports client classes |\n24: | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` |\n25: | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` |\n26: | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` |\n27: | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` |\n28: | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file` |\n29: | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` |\n30: | `agentcube/utils/__init__.py` | Empty (module marker) |\n31: | `examples/basic_usage.py`, `examples/agent_runtime_usage.py`, `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py`, `tests/*.py` | Non-library artifacts |\n32: \n33: ## Public exports (`agentcube/__init__.py`)\n34: \n35: ```python\n36: from .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n37: from .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n38: \n39: __all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n40: ```\n41: \n42: `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` additionally exports (not in root `__all__`):\n43: \n44: ```python\n45: __all__ = [\n46:     \"ControlPlaneClient\",\n47:     \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n48:     \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\",\n49: ]\n50: ```\n51: \n52: ## Configuration (no single `Configuration` class)\n53: \n54: There is **no** dedicated configuration dataclass. Defaults and environment resolution are distributed across:\n55: \n56: | Component | Resolved settings |\n57: |-----------|-------------------|\n58: | `ControlPlaneClient` | `base_url` ÔćÉ `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; `Authorization` ÔćÉ `auth_token` or SA token file; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` |\n59: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | `router_url` ÔćÉ arg or `ROUTER_URL` (required); `workload_manager_url` / `auth_token` passed to `ControlPlaneClient`; `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`, `session_id` |\n60: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`; `base_url` from `base_url` **or** `router_url`+`namespace`+`cr_name` |\n61: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | `router_url` ÔćÉ arg or `ROUTER_URL`; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0` passed to data plane |\n62: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | same timeout defaults as above |\n63: \n64: ## `CodeInterpreterClient` (`agentcube/code_interpreter.py`)\n65: \n66: ```python\n67: class CodeInterpreterClient:\n68:     def __init__(\n69:         self,\n70:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n71:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n72:         ttl: int = 3600,\n73:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n74:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n75:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n76:         verbose: bool = False,\n77:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n78:     ): ...\n79: \n80:     def _init_data_plane(self) -> None: ...\n81: \n82:     def __enter__(self): ...\n83:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n84: \n85:     def stop(self) -> None: ...\n86: \n87:     def execute_command(self, command: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n88:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n89:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n90:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n91:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None: ...\n92:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\"): ...\n93: ```\n94: \n95: **Fields set on instance:** `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`, `logger`, `cp_client`, `router_url`, `session_id`, `dp_client`.\n96: \n97: ## `AgentRuntimeClient` (`agentcube/agent_runtime.py`)\n98: \n99: ```python\n100: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n101:     def __init__(\n102:         self,\n103:         agent_name: str,\n104:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n105:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n106:         verbose: bool = False,\n107:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n108:         timeout: int = 120,\n109:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n110:     ): ...\n111: \n112:     def __enter__(self): ...\n113:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n114: \n115:     def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any: ...\n116: \n117:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n118: ```\n119: \n120: **Fields:** `agent_name`, `namespace`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`, `logger`, `router_url`, `session_id`, `dp_client`.\n121: \n122: ## `ControlPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`)\n123: \n124: ```python\n125: class ControlPlaneClient:\n126:     def __init__(\n127:         self,\n128:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n129:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n130:         timeout: int = 120,\n131:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n132:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n133:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n134:     ): ...\n135: \n136:     def create_session(\n137:         self,\n138:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n139:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n140:         metadata: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n141:         ttl: int = 3600,\n142:     ) -> str: ...\n143: \n144:     def delete_session(self, session_id: str) -> bool: ...\n145: \n146:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n147: ```\n148: \n149: ### Control plane ÔÇö HTTP\n150: \n151: | Method | Path | Notes |\n152: |--------|------|-------|\n153: | `POST` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | JSON body: `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `metadata` |\n154: | `DELETE` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | 404 treated as success in `delete_session` |\n155: \n156: **Headers (default on `self.session`):**\n157: \n158: - `Content-Type`: `application/json`\n159: - `Authorization`: `Bearer {token}` if token non-empty\n160: \n161: **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` on each request.\n162: \n163: ## `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`)\n164: \n165: ```python\n166: class CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n167:     def __init__(\n168:         self,\n169:         session_id: str,\n170:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n171:         namespace: Optional[str] = None,\n172:         cr_name: Optional[str] = None,\n173:         base_url: Optional[str] = None,\n174:         timeout: int = 120,\n175:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n176:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n177:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n178:     ): ...\n179: \n180:     def _request(self, method: str, endpoint: str, body: Optional[bytes] = None, **kwargs) -> requests.Response: ...\n181: \n182:     def execute_command(self, command: Union[str, List[str]], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n183:     def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n184:     def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n185:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n186:     def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None: ...\n187:     def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any: ...\n188:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n189: ```\n190: \n191: ### Data plane (Code Interpreter) ÔÇö base URL\n192: \n193: If `base_url` is not provided:\n194: \n195: ```text\n196: base_path = \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\"\n197: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n198: ```\n199: \n200: ### Data plane ÔÇö HTTP (relative to `self.base_url`)\n201: \n202: | Method | Relative path | Body / params |\n203: |--------|---------------|---------------|\n204: | `POST` | `api/execute` | JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` |\n205: | `POST` | `api/files` | JSON `{\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` |\n206: | `POST` | `api/files` (multipart) | `files={'file': ...}`, `data={'path', 'mode'}` |\n207: | `GET` | `api/files/{clean_path}` | `stream=True` for download (`clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`) |\n208: | `GET` | `api/files` | query `path` |\n209: \n210: **Headers:**\n211: \n212: - Default session header: `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n213: - JSON requests: `Content-Type: application/json` when `body` is set in `_request`\n214: - Multipart upload: `x-agentcube-session-id` only (no JSON Content-Type on the outer request)\n215: \n216: **Note:** Docstring states Router handles JWT; SDK does not set `Authorization` on data plane.\n217: \n218: ## `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` (`agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`)\n219: \n220: ```python\n221: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n222:     SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n223: \n224:     def __init__(\n225:         self,\n226:         router_url: str,\n227:         namespace: str,\n228:         agent_name: str,\n229:         timeout: int = 120,\n230:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n231:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n232:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n233:     ): ...\n234: \n235:     def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str: ...\n236: \n237:     def invoke(\n238:         self,\n239:         session_id: str,\n240:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n241:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n242:     ) -> requests.Response: ...\n243: \n244:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n245: ```\n246: \n247: ### Data plane (Agent Runtime) ÔÇö base URL\n248: \n249: ```text\n250: base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n251: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n252: ```\n253: \n254: ### Data plane ÔÇö HTTP\n255: \n256: | Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n257: |--------|-----|---------|------|\n258: | `GET` | `self.base_url` | (session default headers only) | ÔÇö |\n259: | `POST` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n260: \n261: **Timeouts:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` where `timeout` for `invoke` read side is the method argument or `self.timeout`.\n262: \n263: ## `create_session` (`agentcube/utils/http.py`)\n264: \n265: ```python\n266: def create_session(\n267:     pool_connections: int = 10,\n268:     pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n269: ) -> requests.Session: ...\n270: ```\n271: \n272: Mounts `HTTPAdapter` for `http://` and `https://`.\n273: \n274: ## `read_token_from_file` (`agentcube/utils/utils.py`)\n275: \n276: ```python\n277: def read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str: ...\n278: ```\n279: \n280: Returns file contents stripped, or `\"\"` on `FileNotFoundError`.\n281: \n282: ## `get_logger` (`agentcube/utils/log.py`)\n283: \n284: ```python\n285: def get_logger(name: str, level: Union[int, str] = logging.INFO) -> logging.Logger: ...\n286: ```\n287: \n288: ## Exception hierarchy (`agentcube/exceptions.py`)\n289: \n290: ```python\n291: class AgentCubeError(Exception):\n292:     \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n293:     pass\n294: \n295: class CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n296:     def __init__(self, exit_code, stderr, command=None):\n297:         self.exit_code = exit_code\n298:         self.stderr = stderr\n299:         self.command = command\n300:         super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n301: \n302: class SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n303:     \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"\"\"\n304:     pass\n305: \n306: class DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n307:     \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n308:     pass\n309: ```\n310: \n311: ## Dependencies (`sdk-python/pyproject.toml`)\n312: \n313: ```toml\n314: dependencies = [\n315:     \"requests\",\n316:     \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n317:     \"cryptography\",\n318: ]\n319: ```\n320: \n321: - `requires-python = \">=3.10\"`\n322: - Build: `setuptools>=61.0`, `wheel`; backend `setuptools.build_meta`\n323: - Packages: `where = [\".\"]`, `include = [\"agentcube*\"]`, `namespaces = false`\n324: \n325: \n326: --- python-sdk/spec.md ---\n327: # AgentCube Python SDK Specification\n328: \n329: ## Purpose\n330: \n331: Python client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router.\n332: \n333: ## Requirements\n334: \n335: ### Requirement: `CodeInterpreterClient` lifecycle\n336: The system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n337: \n338: #### Scenario: Context manager cleanup\n339: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager\n340: - **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n341: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes the data-plane session, deletes the control-plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n342: \n343: #### Scenario: Data plane init failure after session create\n344: - **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n345: - **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises\n346: - **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise\n347: \n348: #### Scenario: Router URL required\n349: - **GIVEN** neither `router_url` nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n350: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs\n351: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`\n352: \n353: ### Requirement: Code Interpreter ÔÇö execute, files, stop\n354: The system SHALL expose `execute_command`, `run_code`, `write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`, and `stop` delegating to the data plane client where applicable.\n355: \n356: #### Scenario: Command non-zero exit\n357: - **GIVEN** `execute_command` receives a response with `exit_code != 0`\n358: - **WHEN** the response JSON is parsed\n359: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command`\n360: \n361: #### Scenario: Python code execution path\n362: - **GIVEN** `language` is `python`, `py`, or `python3`\n363: - **WHEN** `run_code` runs\n364: - **THEN** the system SHALL write a timestamped `.py` file via `write_file` and execute `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n365: \n366: ### Requirement: `AgentRuntimeClient` lifecycle\n367: The system SHALL bootstrap or reuse `session_id` from the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint via `GET` on the base invocation URL, then `POST` JSON payloads with session header.\n368: \n369: #### Scenario: Context manager\n370: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n371: - **WHEN** the block exits\n372: - **THEN** `close()` SHALL close the underlying `requests.Session`\n373: \n374: #### Scenario: Bootstrap session id\n375: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is not provided\n376: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n377: - **THEN** it SHALL `GET` `{router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` and read header `x-agentcube-session-id`; if missing, raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n378: \n379: #### Scenario: Invoke without session\n380: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is falsy\n381: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n382: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n383: \n384: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts ÔÇö control plane\n385: The system SHALL use `requests.Session` with connection pooling (`HTTPAdapter`) for Workload Manager calls.\n386: \n387: #### Scenario: Create session\n388: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600)`\n389: - **WHEN** the request succeeds\n390: - **THEN** the client SHALL `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body `{\"name\",\"namespace\",\"ttl\",\"metadata\"}` and return `data[\"sessionId\"]` or raise `ValueError` if absent\n391: \n392: #### Scenario: Delete session\n393: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(session_id)`\n394: - **WHEN** the server returns 404\n395: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`; on other failures it SHALL log and return `False`\n396: \n397: #### Scenario: Workload Manager URL and auth\n398: - **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url` and `auth_token` may be omitted\n399: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n400: - **THEN** `base_url` SHALL resolve from `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; token SHALL resolve from `auth_token` or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` via `read_token_from_file`, and if present set `Authorization: Bearer {token}`\n401: \n402: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts ÔÇö data plane (Code Interpreter)\n403: The system SHALL target Router-relative paths under `{base_url}` derived from `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{ns}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")` unless `base_url` is passed explicitly.\n404: \n405: #### Scenario: Execute command\n406: - **WHEN** `execute_command` posts to `api/execute`\n407: - **THEN** the body SHALL be JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` and read timeout SHALL be `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds when numeric (to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124)\n408: \n409: #### Scenario: Files API\n410: - **WHEN** `write_file` runs\n411: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST api/files` with base64 `content`, `path`, `mode` `\"0644\"`\n412: - **WHEN** `upload_file` runs\n413: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST` multipart to `api/files` with headers including `x-agentcube-session-id`\n414: \n415: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts ÔÇö data plane (Agent Runtime)\n416: The system SHALL `POST` JSON to the invocation base URL with headers `x-agentcube-session-id` and `Content-Type: application/json`.\n417: \n418: #### Scenario: Invoke timeout tuple\n419: - **GIVEN** `invoke(..., timeout=None)`\n420: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n421: - **THEN** `timeout` SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `self.timeout` defaults to `120`\n422: \n423: ### Requirement: Session header management\n424: The system SHALL use lowercase header name `x-agentcube-session-id` for SDK Router requests (`CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` default session header; `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` uses class constant `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`).\n425: \n426: #### Scenario: Code Interpreter session header\n427: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed\n428: - **WHEN** any `_request` or upload runs\n429: - **THEN** the session SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (upload sets it explicitly on the multipart POST)\n430: \n431: ### Requirement: Exception hierarchy\n432: The system SHALL define `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` in `agentcube.exceptions`.\n433: \n434: #### Scenario: Command failure\n435: - **GIVEN** remote command returns non-zero exit code in JSON\n436: - **WHEN** `execute_command` processes the response\n437: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n438: \n439: #### Scenario: SessionError / DataPlaneError usage\n440: - **GIVEN** the current package sources under `agentcube/`\n441: - **WHEN** searching for `raise SessionError` / `raise DataPlaneError`\n442: - **THEN** these classes are defined for extension but not raised by the core client modules in the extracted tree (callers MAY rely on `ValueError`, `requests` exceptions, or `CommandExecutionError`)\n443: \n444: ### Requirement: Timeout behavior\n445: The system SHALL default control-plane and data-plane read timeouts to `120` seconds and connect timeout to `5.0` seconds unless overridden per call.\n446: \n447: #### Scenario: Per-call override for code execution\n448: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=None)`\n449: - **WHEN** `timeout` is `None`\n450: - **THEN** the effective timeout value SHALL default to `self.timeout` (`120`) for constructing the PicoD timeout string and read-timeout buffer logic\n451: \n452: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeClient constructor timeouts\n453: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(..., timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`\n454: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called without `timeout`\n455: - **THEN** read timeout SHALL be `120` (instance default)\n456: \n457: ---\n458: \n459: **Public package surface:** `agentcube/__init__.py` exports only `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` in `__all__`.\n460: \n461: \n462: Previous proposal:\n463: [Stage ST-1 completed]\n464: \n465: Include: architecture, data structures, API contracts, error handling, testing strategy.\n\n(End of file - total 465 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"Write design.md with technical implementation details for the agentcube project:\n\nAR: AR-029 ÔÇö SDK HTTP ň║Ľň▒éň«óŠłĚšź»\nModule: sdk-python\nLanguage: Python\nSize: M\n\nSpecs:\n--- python-sdk/design.md ---\n# AgentCube Python SDK ÔÇö Design\n\nSource root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/`.\n\n## Package layout\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pyproject.toml` | Package `agentcube-sdk`, dependencies |\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports |\n| `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/.sdd_prompt.md","time":{"start":1775876586454,"end":1775876586461}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775876586492,"sessionID":"ses_285821295ffeF8N6eB6GIv9su3","part":{"id":"prt_d7a7e3bdf001PwhQIUGDcWJor8","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7a7e1eed0013D3kHezV4TZveL","sessionID":"ses_285821295ffeF8N6eB6GIv9su3","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":29911,"input":14906,"output":99,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":14906}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775876590570,"sessionID":"ses_285821295ffeF8N6eB6GIv9su3","part":{"id":"prt_d7a7e4be8001LsJAURwixLvLAp","messageID":"msg_d7a7e3c12001acQYhg310tf14q","sessionID":"ses_285821295ffeF8N6eB6GIv9su3","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876647757,"sessionID":"ses_285821295ffeF8N6eB6GIv9su3","part":{"id":"prt_d7a7e5f81001srb3L7bAhEeHM0","messageID":"msg_d7a7e3c12001acQYhg310tf14q","sessionID":"ses_285821295ffeF8N6eB6GIv9su3","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_53a7c908a296413195a920a1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-034: CI/CD GitHub Actions\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement comprehensive GitHub Actions CI/CD infrastructure for the AgentCube project, consisting of 12 automated workflows covering build verification, linting, testing, code generation, end-to-end testing, release automation, and contributor workflow approvals.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nThe AgentCube project requires robust CI/CD automation to ensure code quality, catch regressions early, and automate release processes. The project consists of multiple components:\n\n- **Go-based Workload Manager** (`workload-manager`)\n- **Go-based AgentD Controller** (`agentd`)\n- **Python SDK** (`sdk-python`)\n- **Kubernetes manifests and Helm charts**\n\nThe current manual build and test processes need automation through GitHub Actions to support:\n1. Pull request validation on multiple code paths\n2. Multi-architecture Docker image building and publishing\n3. End-to-end testing in Kind clusters\n4. Release automation with semantic versioning\n5. Code quality enforcement (linting, spelling, copyright headers)\n\n### Goal\n\nImplement 12 GitHub Actions workflows in `.github/workflows/` that:\n\n- Run on pull requests to `main` and `release-*` branches\n- Use path filtering to avoid unnecessary runs\n- Build and push Docker images to GitHub Container Registry\n- Run Go and Python tests with coverage reporting\n- Perform code generation drift checks\n- Execute end-to-end tests on Kind clusters\n- Enforce spelling and copyright compliance\n- Automate plugin publishing and workflow approvals\n\n### Value\n\n| Benefit | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| **Automation** | Eliminates manual build/test/release steps |\n| **Consistency** | Ensures all PRs pass identical checks |\n| **Speed** | Path filtering skips irrelevant workflows |\n| **Reliability** | E2E tests catch integration issues |\n| **Release Efficiency** | Automated image publishing on tags |\n| **Quality** | Lint, spelling, copyright enforcement |\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In-Scope\n\n| Workflow | Path | Description |\n|----------|------|-------------|\n| Agentcube CI Workflow | `.github/workflows/main.yml` | Docker build on PR |\n| Lint | `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | Go lint with golangci-lint |\n| Codegen Check | `.github/workflows/codegen-check.yml` | Verify generated code up-to-date |\n| Test Coverage | `.github/workflows/test-coverage.yml` | Go test with coverage |\n| E2E Tests | `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` | End-to-end testing on Kind |\n| Python SDK Tests | `.github/workflows/python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK unit tests |\n| Python Lint | `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml` | Ruff Python linting |\n| Codespell | `.github/workflows/codespell.yml` | Spelling check |\n| Copyright Check | `.github/workflows/copyright-check.yml` | Copyright header enforcement |\n| Build and Push Release Images | `.github/workflows/build-push-release.yml` | Multi-arch image publishing |\n| Dify Plugin Publish | `.github/workflows/dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Plugin release automation |\n| Approve Workflows | `.github/workflows/workflows-approve.yml` | First-time contributor approval |\n\n### Out-of-Scope\n\n- Jenkins or other CI systems\n- Cloud-specific deployments (AWS, GCP)\n- Custom GitHub runners\n- Performance benchmarking CI\n- Security scanning (Dependabot covers dependencies)\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Purpose | Status |\n|------------|---------|--------|\n| `docker/setup-buildx-action` | Docker buildx setup | Required |\n| `docker/login-action` | GHCR login | Required for releases |\n| `actions/checkout` | Repository checkout | Required |\n| `actions/setup-go` | Go environment | Required |\n| `actions/setup-python` | Python environment | Required for Python workflows |\n| `helm/kind-action` | Kind cluster creation | Required for E2E |\n| `dorny/paths-filter` | Path-based filtering | Required |\n| `codecov/codecov-action` | Coverage upload | Optional |\n| `aws-actions/configure-aws-credentials` | AWS ECR (future) | Not in initial scope |\n| `docker/build-push-action` | Multi-platform builds | Required |\n\n### Upstream\n\n- `ci-cd/spec.md` ÔÇö Requirements document\n- `ci-cd/design.md` ÔÇö Technical design specifications\n- `Makefile` ÔÇö Build targets referenced by workflows\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n1. **Contributors** ÔÇö All PRs trigger workflow runs\n2. **Release managers** ÔÇö Tag pushes trigger image publishing\n3. **End users** ÔÇö Benefit from tested releases\n4. **External plugins** ÔÇö Dify plugin publishing workflow\n\n### Risks\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| Workflow run timeouts | Medium | Path filtering reduces unnecessary runs; separate jobs |\n| Flaky E2E tests | Medium | Artifact collection on failure; retry logic |\n| Concurrent workflow limits | Low | Queue management; prioritize main branch |\n| Secret exposure | High | Use GitHub secrets; minimize secret usage |\n| Dependabot workflow changes | Low | Pin action versions; review updates |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Option 1: Single monolithic workflow (Not Selected)\n\n**Pros**: Single trigger, simpler structure\n**Cons**: No parallel execution; path filtering not granular; harder to debug\n\n### Option 2: CircleCI or Jenkins (Not Selected)\n\n**Pros**: Mature platforms\n**Cons**: Vendor lock-in; requires infrastructure; inconsistent with GitHub ecosystem\n\n### Option 3: GitLab CI (Not Selected)\n\n**Pros**: Built-in Auto DevOps\n**Cons**: Project not on GitLab; additional platform to maintain\n\n### Option 4: 12 separate workflow files (Selected)\n\n**Pros**: Fine-grained path filtering; parallel execution; clear separation of concerns; each workflow can be debugged independently\n**Cons**: More files to maintain; shared conventions require discipline\n\n---\n\n## Technical Design\n\n### Workflow Summary\n\n| # | Filename | Trigger | Path Filter | Key Jobs |\n|---|----------|---------|-------------|----------|\n| 1 | `main.yml` | PR: main, release-* | (none) | build |\n| 2 | `lint.yml` | PR: main, release-* | `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `.golangci.yml` | golangci |\n| 3 | `codegen-check.yml` | PR: main, release-* | `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` | codegen-check |\n| 4 | `test-coverage.yml` | PR, merge_group, workflow_call | `**` minus md/svg/png/docs | coverage |\n| 5 | `e2e.yml` | PR: main, release-* | (none) | e2e-test |\n| 6 | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | PR, merge_group | `sdk-python/**` | python-sdk-tests |\n| 7 | `python-lint.yml` | PR: main, release-* | `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `pyproject.toml` | python_lint |\n| 8 | `codespell.yml` | PR: main, release-* | (none) | codespell |\n| 9 | `copyright-check.yml` | PR: main, release-* | copyright: all except md/svg/png/docs/.github | build |\n| 10 | `build-push-release.yml` | push: main, tags v*.*.* | (none) | build-and-push |\n| 11 | `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | push: tags dify-plugin/v* | (none) | publish |\n| 12 | `workflows-approve.yml` | PR: main, release-** | (logic-based) | approve |\n\n### Trigger Details\n\n**Pull Request Triggers:**\n- `main` branch ÔÇö primary development branch\n- `release-*` pattern ÔÇö release branches\n\n**Push Triggers:**\n- `main` branch ÔÇö for latest image builds\n- Semantic version tags: `v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*` (e.g., `v1.2.3`, `v1.2.3-beta`)\n- Dify plugin tags: `dify-plugin/v*`\n\n### Path Filters\n\nUses `dorny/paths-filter` for efficient workflow triggering:\n\n| Filter Name | Patterns |\n|-------------|----------|\n| lint | `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml` |\n| codegen | `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` |\n| coverage | `**` (all) minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**` |\n| copyright | All except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**` |\n| python | `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml` |\n| sdk | `sdk-python/**` |\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Workflow | Variable | Value |\n|----------|----------|-------|\n| E2E | `ARTIFACTS_PATH` | `${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs` |\n| Release | `TAG` | `github.ref_name` (tag) or `latest` |\n| Release | `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` |\n\n### Secrets Required\n\n| Secret | Purpose | Workflows |\n|--------|---------|------------|\n| `GITHUB_TOKEN` | GHCR login, workflow approval | build-push-release, workflows-approve |\n| `CODECOV_TOKEN` | Coverage upload (optional) | test-coverage |\n| `GH_TOKEN` | Cross-repo plugin PR | dify-plugin-publish |\n\n### Key Make Targets\n\n| Target | Workflow | Purpose |\n|--------|----------|---------|\n| `docker-build` | main.yml | Build workload manager image |\n| `docker-build-router` | e2e.yml | Build router image |\n| `docker-build-picod` | e2e.yml | Build picod image |\n| `docker-buildx-push` | build-push-release.yml | Push workload manager |\n| `docker-buildx-push-router` | build-push-release.yml | Push router image |\n| `docker-buildx-push-picod` | build-push-release.yml | Push picod image |\n| `lint` | lint.yml | Run golangci-lint |\n| `gen-check` | codegen-check.yml | Verify code generation |\n| `gen-copyright` | copyright-check.yml | Generate copyright headers |\n| `e2e` | e2e.yml | Run E2E tests |\n| `e2e-clean` | e2e.yml | Cleanup Kind cluster |\n\n### Go Version Matrix\n\n| Workflow | Go Version |\n|----------|-------------|\n| lint.yml | 1.24 |\n| codegen-check.yml | 1.24.4 |\n| test-coverage.yml | 1.24 |\n| e2e.yml | 1.23 |\n| build-push-release.yml | 1.24.4 |\n\n### Python Version Matrix\n\n| Workflow | Python Version |\n|----------|----------------|\n| python-sdk-tests.yml | 3.12 |\n| python-lint.yml | 3.10 |\n| codespell.yml | (system) |\n\n### E2E Test Infrastructure\n\n**Kind Cluster:**\n- Name: `agentcube-e2e`\n- Kind version: v0.30.0\n- Created by: `kind create cluster` in `run_e2e.sh`\n\n**CRD Installation:**\n- Downloads agent-sandbox v0.1.1 by default\n- Applies manifest.yaml and extensions.yaml\n\n**Images Pre-loaded:**\n- `workloadmanager:latest` (built locally)\n- `agentcube-router:latest` (built locally)\n- `picod:latest` (built locally)\n- `redis:7-alpine` (pulled)\n- `python:3.9-slim` (pulled)\n\n**Port Forwards:**\n- Workload Manager: 8080 Ôćĺ service/workloadmanager:8080\n- Router: 8081 Ôćĺ service/agentcube-router:8080\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Core Build & Lint Workflows\n\n- [ ] Create `.github/workflows/main.yml` ÔÇö Docker build verification\n- [ ] Create `.github/workflows/lint.yml` ÔÇö Go lint with path filter\n- [ ] Create `.github/workflows/codegen-check.yml` ÔÇö Code generation verification\n\n### Phase 2: Testing Workflows\n\n- [ ] Create `.github/workflows/test-coverage.yml` ÔÇö Go coverage tests\n- [ ] Create `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` ÔÇö Kind-based E2E tests\n- [ ] Create `.github/workflows/python-sdk-tests.yml` ÔÇö Python SDK tests\n- [ ] Create `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml` ÔÇö Ruff Python lint\n\n### Phase 3: Quality Enforcement Workflows\n\n- [ ] Create `.github/workflows/codespell.yml` ÔÇö Spelling checks\n- [ ] Create `.github/workflows/copyright-check.yml` ÔÇö Header enforcement\n\n### Phase 4: Release & Automation Workflows\n\n- [ ] Create `.github/workflows/build-push-release.yml` ÔÇö Image publishing\n- [ ] Create `.github/workflows/dify-plugin-publish.yml` ÔÇö Plugin release\n- [ ] Create `.github/workflows/workflows-approve.yml` ÔÇö Contributor approval\n\n### Phase 5: Integration\n\n- [ ] Add workflow dispatch for manual runs\n- [ ] Configure required status checks\n- [ ] Verify path filtering works correctly\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n|----|----------|-----------------|\n| CI-001 | PR to main with Go changes | lint.yml and test-coverage.yml run |\n| CI-002 | PR to main with Python changes | python-lint.yml and python-sdk-tests.yml run |\n| CI-003 | PR with no relevant changes | No workflows trigger (path filter) |\n| CI-004 | Push to main branch | main.yml builds Docker image |\n| CI-005 | Tag push v1.0.0 | build-push-release.yml publishes images with tag v1.0.0 |\n| CI-006 | E2E workflow failure | Logs collected in e2e-logs artifact |\n| CI-007 | Codegen drift detected | Workflow fails with exit code |\n| CI-008 | Missing copyright header | copyright-check.yml fails |\n| CI-009 | Typo in code | codespell.yml fails |\n| CI-010 | First-time contributor PR | workflows-approve.yml queues for approval |\n| CI-011 | Dify plugin tag push | dify-plugin-publish.yml creates PR |\n| CI-012 | Workflow call from external | test-coverage.yml runs with optional token |\n\n---\n\n## Timeline Estimate\n\n| Phase | Workflows | Effort |\n|-------|-----------|--------|\n| Phase 1: Core Build & Lint | main, lint, codegen-check | 4 hours |\n| Phase 2: Testing | test-coverage, e2e, python-sdk-tests, python-lint | 6 hours |\n| Phase 3: Quality Enforcement | codespell, copyright-check | 2 hours |\n| Phase 4: Release & Automation | build-push-release, dify-plugin-publish, workflows-approve | 4 hours |\n| Phase 5: Integration | Testing, documentation | 2 hours |\n| **Total** | **12 workflows** | **18 hours** |\n\n---\n\n## Relationship to Other ARs\n\nThis AR (AR-034) provides the CI/CD infrastructure that supports all other AgentCube implementation ARs:\n\n- **AR-029** (SDK HTTP Client) ÔÇö Verified by python-sdk-tests.yml\n- **Future ARs** ÔÇö Will use these workflows for validation\n\nThe CI/CD infrastructure is foundationalÔÇöwithout it, other ARs cannot be properly validated before merging.","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775876647688,"end":1775876647754}}}}
